    en: "A New York worker who gets hurt on the job picks the doctor. Section 13-a of the Workers' Compensation Law lets an injured worker choose any provider on the state Workers' Compensation Board (WCB) list. The employer cannot force a specific clinic, except in narrow Preferred Provider Organization setups for the first 30 days or for independent medical exams. The worker can switch doctors at any time. Pressuring a worker or a doctor is a misdemeanor. The WCB keeps a public list of approved providers at wcb.ny.gov. The worker pays nothing out of pocket."
